{
  "stem": "1415.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were just like taken away in the morning, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] very few came back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember there were a lot of kids that came and never came back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And our-- our barrack looked different than the others.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly what it looked like, but it didn't look the same as the other barracks.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was block 17, I mean seven.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Number seven.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had something about numbers, that I remember.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when we got to that camp, like I say, there were a lot of twins then taken away, and it was a lot of elimination taking place as we were coming in to that camp.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I noticed in our block, and there were not too many-- too many blocks occupied in that camp, not too many.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] During that time when I was in there, I found my brother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My oldest brother was right across in the next camp across from us, in D lager.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- one-- one day, he got a hold of somebody from our hometown, and-- and they told me-- to get me, and I went near-- See, the end of the-- the end of the barrack was also a door to go out, and you faced the-- the electric fences on that side.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The front side is where-- where the walkway, where the barracks sort of head to head each other.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This was the back side of the barrack.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "On the backside of the barracks were the electric fences on either side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So there were even and odd barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we were on the odd side, and we were right next to the D camp, which was the men's camp, and that's where my brother was.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
